directory: crates/ctx-cage/tests
summary: Integration test suite for ctx-cage, exercising each subsystem — broker, bwrap sandbox argv construction, crate discovery, CLI mode resolution, wire protocol, proxy header rewriting, and summarize staleness — largely in isolation from real subprocesses, sockets, or network I/O.

Tests fall into two styles: pure logic checks (bwrap_build, cli, protocol, summarize) that assert on constructed values or in-memory buffers with no I/O, and end-to-end checks (broker_loopback, proxy) that drive real `UnixListener`/`UnixStream` pairs with fake spawners/upstreams standing in for subprocesses and network connections. Any test spawning a background thread against a Unix socket (broker_loopback, proxy) must use a unique socket/temp path derived from pid + atomic counter to survive parallel test execution — this pattern is duplicated independently in both files rather than shared, so a new socket-based test should follow the same convention rather than introduce a third variant.

`common/` is the only shared fixture module, supplying synthetic `BwrapConfig`/`ClaudeBinds` and pure argv predicates to bwrap-related tests; it holds no filesystem or process state, unlike the ad hoc tempdir helpers each integration test file defines for itself (bwrap_discover, cli's task_file_is_read_from_disk).

Coupling to watch: bwrap_build.rs and common/ both assume the constant names (`CAGE_BIN`, `CAGE_RULES_PATH`, `CAGE_RUN_DIR`) and `BwrapConfig` shape from `ctx_cage::bwrap` — renaming or restructuring that module requires updating both. Similarly, cli.rs mirrors the `Cli`/`Mode`/`ResolveError` shapes from `ctx_cage::cli`, and proxy.rs mirrors header-rewrite rules from `ctx_cage::proxy`; each is a single point of duplication between production and test code that must be updated together.

No intent.md exists for this directory.